","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"6372c076-6c9b-5d73-a748-8b8f82187ed4","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"7e4fff6f-e0ff-5958-824d-2613bf441de4","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"b6feb235-6eca-5423-9a56-7c39025cfccc","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"e5915315-219d-50d8-a14c-f43dbe0af10d","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"4029ee68-9da4-5dbc-b713-2744f953300c","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"9a1ea071-726f-5ade-89c0-37ac012f2f13","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"b00edd06-8e4f-525b-8ef7-c13a9dbb324e","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"aa77dfb3-b03c-5bea-92a5-3e58240cb4fe","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-6ac","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 1053a5d1-be74-4f2c-93d6-ac32b108ef06 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 1053a5d1-be74-4f2c-93d6-ac32b108ef06 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 6acdcdf4-b404-495a-8892-742a85f1e494 --><!-- begin field 17e199b4-cdde-4cc9-b54c-8dfdb583b033 --><p>The recommendations on identifying Achilles tendon rupture are based on expert opinion in the review articles <em>Management of chronic ruptures of the Achilles tendon</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Maffulli, 2008</a>], <em>Achilles tendon rupture</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Boyd, 2015</a>], <em>Everything Achilles: knowledge update and current concepts in management: AAOS exhibit selection </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Uquillas, 2015</a>], <em>Pain at the back of the heel</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Morton, 2016</a>], and <em>Acute Achilles tendon rupture </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Singh, 2017</a>].  </p><ul><li>Achilles tendon rupture is missed by non-specialists in about 20% of cases [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Singh, 2017</a>]. </li><li>Prompt diagnosis is important because delay in treatment can lead to poorer outcomes, including disability, more complicated surgery, and inability to return to sporting activity [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/achilles-tendinopathy/references/\">Singh, 2017</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 17e199b4-cdde-4cc9-b54c-8dfdb583b033 --><!-- end item 6acdcdf4-b404-495a-8892-742a85f1e494 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}